entry.title: NEWS.am digest: Pelosi condemns illegal attacks by Azerbaijan on Armenia; latest highlights

media:group.media:title: NEWS.am digest: Pelosi condemns illegal attacks by Azerbaijan on Armenia; latest highlights
media:group.media:description:
Armenian News - NEWS.am presents the breaking news as of 18.09.22:
PELOSI IN ARMENIA https://news.am/eng/news/720851.html
U.S. House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi strongly condemned illegal border attacks by Azerbaijan on Armenia during a high-profile trip to Yerevan on Sunday.
“This was initiated by the Azerbaijanis,” Ms. Pelosi said at a news conference during her visit to Armenia. “There has to be recognition of that.” "We strongly condemn those attacks," she added in a joint news conference with Armenian parliamentary speaker Alen Simonyan.
Pelosi said that she wanted to convey “the strong and ongoing support of the United States” for Armenia but also called for a negotiated settlement.
Pelosi's remarks drew a strong rebuke from Baku. "The unsubstantiated and unfair accusations leveled by Pelosi against Azerbaijan are unacceptable," the foreign ministry said in a statement.
"This is a serious blow to the efforts to normalize relations between Armenia and Azerbaijan," the ministry said. https://news.am/eng/news/720853.html
The United States, Pelosi said, was listening to Armenia about what its defense needs were and said Washington wanted to help and support Armenia in what she cast as a global struggle between democracy and autocracy.
"We should be using our influence, our leverage showing that Armenian democracy and sovereignty are a priority," Pelosi said.
Representative Frank Pallone who was traveling with Ms. Pelosi added: “The United States is very concerned about Armenia’s security and we want to do whatever we can to be more supportive of Armenia’s security,” he said.
https://news.am/eng/news/720854.html
Alen Simonyan, the speaker of Armenia’s parliament in turn said that Armenia expects active support for its democracy, sovereignty, and territorial integrity in all possible directions.
PASHINYAN MEETS PELOSI https://news.am/eng/news/720899.html
Armenia’s Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan noted during his meeting with Nancy Pelosi that the Armenian side appreciates the clear position of the US regarding Azerbaijan's aggression against Armenia.
Nancy Pelosi, thanking Nikol Pashinyan, noted that the US stands by Armenia in all respects.
“Support for democracy in Armenia, the Armenian Genocide recognition resolution, countering Turkey in the Nagorno Karabakh issue, and in all other issues we are Armenia's friend,” she noted.
https://news.am/eng/news/720884.html
Pelosi also met with Armenian opposition Parliament members. Following the meeting the Parliament members told reporters that they have stressed the need to stop aid to Azerbaijan.
Ishkhan Saghatelyan, a member of the 'Armenia' opposition faction, told reporters: "We very clearly conveyed our position that it is unacceptable for us that the US supports Azerbaijan. We are talking about military and political support,” he added.
ARMENIAN GENOCIDE https://news.am/eng/news/720830.html
Earlier Nancy Pelosi laid flowers at the Armenian Genocide Memorial in Yerevan honoring the nearly 1.5 million Armenian victims.
https://news.am/eng/news/720867 .html
During her speech on Sunday at the Cafesjian art center, she noted that what they saw today at the memorial was very thrilling.
Further she said that those 1,5 million killed Armenians are the ancestors of American Armenians living in the US today.
In order to heal the open wounds, the world must recognize the crime, which was nothing but genocide, she added. _____________
